observations.recommendation:
We recommended that:

the Municipal Mayor in coordination with the Sangguniang Bayan adopt and implement guidelines in the claim of communication expenses taking into consideration the limits on the amounts to be claimed as well as the personnel who are qualified or entitled to claim such amounts;


the Municipal Accountant ensure that all claims for communication allowance are supported by certification signed by agency head or his authorized representative that the amounts claimed are used for official purposes only;
Management consider the use of mobile phone fixed plan offered by telecom networks for elected officials and department heads, and that any amount in excess of the plan amount shall be charged against the personal account of the claimant; and purchase in bulk of prepaid load cards for all qualified/entitled  rank in file employees/staff following the required procurement procedures and distribute the same in accordance with the guidelines set; and


the Municipal Budget Officer submit the SB Resolutions realigning funds supporting the herein disbursement for communication expenses if there were any, and ensure that disbursements are at all times supported by an Appropriation Ordinance or law.

We recommended that:
the Municipal Mayor in coordination with the SB adopt and implement guidelines in the claim of communication expenses taking into consideration the limits on the amounts to be claimed as well as the personnel who are qualified/entitled to claim such amounts;
the Municipal Accountant ensure that all claims for communication allowance are supported by certification signed by agency head or his authorized representative that the amounts claimed are used for official purposes only;
Management consider the use of mobile phone fixed plan offered by telecommunication networks for elected officials and department heads, and that any amount in excess of the plan amount shall be charged against the personal account of the claimant; and purchase in bulk of prepaid load cards for all qualified/entitled rank in file employees/staff following the required procurement procedures and distribute the same in accordance with the guidelines set; and
the Municipal Budget Officer submit the SB Resolutions realigning funds supporting the herein disbursement for communication expenses if there were any, and ensure that disbursements are at all times supported by an Appropriation Ordinance or law.

We recommended that Management:

strictly adhere to government’s procurement law to ensure that transparency, accountability, equity, efficiency, and economy in the LGU’s procurement process are observed;



establish petty cash fund, if necessary, for small amounts of expenses and limit reimbursement on necessary procurements only and ensure that all required supporting documents are submitted.

We recommended that the Management:
exert effort for the approval of the LGUs SWM Plan;
monitor the implementation of the existing programs on segregation and collection of garbage;
adopt additional specific revenue-generating measure to promote the viability of the LGU’s Solid Waste Management Plan;
hasten the establishment and construction of LGU’s MRF and/or sanitary land fill as well as assistance to barangays for them to be able to establish their own MRF; and
prepare and submit annual SWM Accomplishment Report.
